        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 8:03PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 756 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of thunderstorms
entering southwest Cascade county, moving northeast at 35 mph. In
addition to lightning, a period of rain and gusty winds to 40 mph
are expected with the arrival of the thunderstorms, with this
activity reaching the Great Falls area around 900 PM.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph in addition to lightning and a
period of rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Cascade, Belt, Black Eagle, Fort  Shaw, Fort Shaw,
Malmstrom Afb, Eden, Stockett, Tracy, Vaughn, First Peoples Buffalo
Jump State Park, Centerville, Sun River, Tower Rock State Park,
Armington, Ulm, and Sand Coulee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
